WARNING:HOTPLUG_SECTION: Using __devinit is unnecessary
#48: FILE: drivers/input/serio/maceps2.c:121:
+static struct serio * __devinit maceps2_allocate_port(int idx)

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*serio)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct serio)...)
#53: FILE: drivers/input/serio/maceps2.c:125:
+	serio = kzalloc(sizeof(struct serio), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

